                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Churchill</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="68" type="source" xml:id="d180fn68">Telegram sent to the
                        Ambassador in Greece for delivery to Prime Minister Churchill. Copy obtained
                        from the Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N.Y.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-26">26 December
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>680. Replying to your 858, I have asked our Ambassador to call upon you as soon
                    as possible and I am ready to be of all assistance I can in this difficult
                    situation.</p>
                <p>I hope that your presence there on the spot will result in achieving an entirely
                    satisfactory solution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
